<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My First Web Page</title>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Heading -->
    <h1>Welcome to My First Web Page</h1>

    <!-- Paragraph -->
    <p>This is a simple web page created using <b>HTML</b>. It includes different elements like headings, paragraphs, and lists.</p>

    <!-- Text formatting -->
    <p>HTML stands for <i>HyperText Markup Language</i>. It is used to design the structure of web pages.</p>

    <!-- Ordered List -->
    <h2>Steps to Create a Web Page</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Open any code editor (like Visual Studio Code).</li>
        <li>Write HTML code.</li>
        <li>Save the file with a .html extension.</li>
        <li>Open it in a browser.</li>
    </ol>

    <!-- Unordered List -->
    <h2>HTML Tags Used</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>&lt;h1&gt; to &lt;h6&gt; - Headings</li>
        <li>&lt;p&gt; - Paragraph</li>
        <li>&lt;b&gt; - Bold Text</li>
        <li>&lt;i&gt; - Italic Text</li>
        <li>&lt;ol&gt; and &lt;ul&gt; - Lists</li>
    </ul>

    <p><b>Conclusion:</b> This experiment helps in understanding the basic structure and formatting of an HTML web page.</p>
</body>
</html>
